# CSS Styling

- Plain CSS only — one file per component in `src/styles/ComponentName/`
- Use CSS variables from `src/styles/Common/Globals.css` for colors and shared values
- Mobile-first responsive design with media queries
- BEM-like or semantic class/ID names (existing code uses IDs heavily — match surrounding style)
- Import `animate.css` classes via components, not in CSS files directly

## Theming

Dark/light theme via CSS variables toggled by `useTheme` hook. Check `Globals.css` before adding hard-coded colors.

## Shared styles

- `Globals.css` — variables, resets, base typography
- `hover.css` — shared hover effects
- `animation.css` — hand-picked animate.css subset + spring-in
- `SkipLink.css` — skip-to-content accessibility link
- `Scrollbar.css` — custom scrollbar styling

Run `yarn lint:css:fix` to auto-fix Stylelint issues.
